{
  "texts": [
    "Taking on agentive, central roles in personally meaningful, scaffolded AI design projects cultivated children's data agency and ownership of their learning process.",
    "Children's pre-and post tests showed that their data-driven explanations of algorithmic bias improved significantly, indicating a more critical understanding of how AI-based systems should be designed or redesigned (Vartiainen et al., 2024).",
    "The study's theoretical and pedagogical insights, alongside its empirically validated framework for scaffolding data-driven design, offer research-based guidance for advancing culturally relevant, equitable, and inclusive AI education.",
    "We suggest that such AI education will help children build their data agency: their ability and volition to be active, contributing members and critical makers of the data-driven society.",
    "Empowering students to shape the future: Understanding AI/ML learning difficulties in K-12 education"
  ]
}